@startuml
title OTW/AfricaStage Collaborative Positive-Selection Workflow

start

:User submits PhotographerDelivery link
(e.g., Google Photos shared album);

:Server registers PhotographerDelivery;
:Server discovers source images;
:Server creates or refreshes source manifest;

if (Discovery successful?) then (yes)
  :Server imports/copies images to ImageServer;
  :Server records canonical ImageAsset URLs
  on AfricaStage/OTW ImageServer;
else (no)
  :Mark PhotographerDelivery as Failed;
  stop
endif

:Server creates ReviewRun;
:ReviewRun state -> Open / CollectingSelections;

fork
  :Reviewer A marks liked images
  (positive checkmarks);
  :Server persists SelectionMarks;
fork again
  :Reviewer B marks liked images
  (positive checkmarks);
  :Server persists SelectionMarks;
fork again
  :Reviewer N marks liked images
  (positive checkmarks);
  :Server persists SelectionMarks;
end fork

:Server aggregates SelectionMarks per ImageAsset;
:Apply selection retention rule
(e.g., retain if marks >= policy threshold);
:Persist selected candidates;

if (Selected set too large?) then (yes)
  :Optional CurationDecision step;
  :Consolidate/prune selected candidates;
else (no)
endif

if (Storage-saving needed later?) then (yes)
  :Create pruning/removal candidates
  as explicit later process;
else (no)
endif

if (Need another pass from same delivery?) then (yes)
  :Start new ReviewRun from same PhotographerDelivery;
else (no)
endif

stop

note right
Modeling constraints:
- No positive SelectionMark is neutral, not rejection.
- Positive selection can be sufficient for retention,
  depending on policy.
- Curation/pruning is explicit and later, not review-time rejection.
- Source share links are ingest-only references.
- Canonical runtime image URLs live on ImageServer after import.
end note

@enduml
